review_text: The staff are so awesome and helpful. I always buy or rent musical instruments from them and I am very happy of the service that I receive each time.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for the 5-star review Farzad. Were very glad youre having a great experience with us. See you again!

review_text: I like review music books here since there has abundance of information which I need, and I also like to stay a while trying various instruments, the staffs here are specialized and welcomed!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Lively, thank you for your review! We are happy that you enjoy spending time in our store and look forward to seeing you soon in White Rock!

review_text: I was trying to sell my fathers accordion and I was quite lost as to where to start. Luckily Drew was super helpful to point me in the right direction. Thank you so much!
response_from_owner_text: Hi Diana, thank you for your review! We are glad to hear that you had a great experience with Drew, and we hope all worked out well for you with your fathers accordion!

review_text: Every year we rent equipment for our car show @ White Rock Dodge, Drew and his team are true professionals that know they stuff. Thank you
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Kam! To many more years ahead! We will be sure to reach out to the White Rock location to share your feedback.

review_text: I got amazing service today. I came in looking for a guitar pedal for my Daughter. The White Rock store did not have the pedal I was looking for and the Woman that helped me(forgive me, I forgot her name) called Winnipeg and Halifax to find it for me. That Women went the extra mile for and I really appreciate the effort.  I am in the market for a Bass and will definitely go to the White Rock L&M for it after todays experience.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you, Nigel! Our team is always dedicated to providing the best service we can! We appreciate your positive review and look forward to seeing you again!

review_text: Little back story I had two Taylor Guitars that both had the same malfunction in the neck! Wild. But Gerald the Manager was very accommodating and went above and beyond and out of his way to assist me in the process. He deserves a Raise!! The other staff are all fantastic as well. Ive never had such a good and warm environment while shopping for music supplies. I fully trust Long&McQuade and I will never buy another guitar from anywhere else! Thanks guys and keep on rocking in the free world..hopefully!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you, Ryan! Our team is always dedicated to providing the best service we can and were glad to hear Gerald could help! We appreciate your positive review and look forward to seeing you again!

review_text: Incredibly knowledgeable, courteous, and friendly. I highly recommend this store for your musical needs. Youll be well taken care of. The prices are fair and the selection is decent. It s one of the smaller stores in the franchise, but it ll still meet all of your needs. Well done!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you Nicholas!

review_text: Small store but they have all the general needs covered. They re also helpful when it comes to locating a product you want, whether by shipping it or redirecting you to another local branch that has it in stock.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much, Curtis! Our network of stores enables us to find the right product for our customers, even if its not something our store would normally carry! We are pleased to hear that our team has been helpful and we hope to see you again soon!

review_text: I had to return a keyboard which I didn t un register, which makes it hard for the store to do the return. I had driven 45 minutes and I was floored I would have to return back home and then come back. One of the employees Chloe was kind enough to call the company and sort it out. Staff going beyond there job.
response_from_owner_text: Were glad we could provide you with amazing customer service! Thank you for your review!

review_text: Great experience at this L&M. We didnt get his name but he helped us with a microphone, tonal differences between Strats - Squier partscaster vs. American pro - and a Godin Progression HT. Store is far for us but we will be back for the excellent customer service. Thank you.
Always rent from Long & McQuade. Kudos to the staff for dealing with my issue for a product that was not available to rent while managing multiple other customers at the same time. Thanks!
response_from_owner_text: Thanks Michael! We are proud to be your go-to place for rentals and look forward to seeing you again!

review_text: When youre buying something like a musical instrument it is important you get the knowledgeable guidance. Buying off of the internet can lead to bad choices.This is a great place to get your musical equipment. The staff is friendly and helpful but more importantly genuinely want to sell you what you need according to your objectives and skills. That means they are not at all pushing and dont try to up sell you, but rather try to find you what truly fits your needs. I find I can trust their integrity. Ive been very happy with everything Ive bought there.
response_from_owner_text: Thank you very much Guy for the great review! We are glad that you enjoy shopping at our store and get the help you need from our staff!

review_text: I have only ever rented speakers and equipment from them but they are always helpful and professional. Ive noticed they have a ton of beautiful instruments and other music related equipment. Seems like the place to go for anything music related.

I went to buy a studio microphone for first time at this location, then I met a guy called Tony scrace a sales and rental associate, who helped me like a king, with this experience I wish to go buy again Tony scrace is the best.
response_from_owner_text: We appreciate your review, Simon!

review_text: Good 1st experience. The guys were real nice and willing to help. They walked me through everything I needed help with. They answered all my beginner level questions. To someone whos new to all this, it sounds like they know their stuff. Thanks guys.
response_from_owner_text: You are very welcome Amit and thank you for the review!

review_text: Best music store around.  All the staff are top notch.  The lesson centre has great teachers and friendly staff. Keep up the good work

review_text: I went over there to purchase a piano book and get some information about buying a new piano. Jamie was so helpful and friendly, she spent a lot of time to give me the correct information about different models, it was my first time at this branch which gave me a great impression.

review_text: Have been a long-time customer of Long & McQuade. Always pleasant staff... Find the specialist for your instrument, their  knowledge with product is amazing. review_text: Always friendly and informative. Staff know their stuff undeniably, and always happy to help answer questions. I do think they should add a few more instruments that are geared towards more advanced players, ie. 7/8 strings, fanned frets, etc. a great deal of run-of-the-mill guitars for the starter player.

review_text: Enjoyed the service, thanks Chad and everyone. Love my new guitar, best price ever!!!! Seagull Rosewood Maritime Sws Dreadnought with on board electronics and it kicks....

review_text: Great selection of instruments and above and beyond customer service.  Big thanks to Girard and Will for making my trip there to buy a new guitar a pleasant and rewarding experience.
We came in 10 minutes before they closed because we had a base reserved that we wanted to pick up. We felt bad that we came in 10 minutes before closing, but they were extremely nice and helpful.
Staff were friendly but respectful of distance. Well informed, honest. Purchased a guitar. Enjoyed the experience.

review_text: Great spot but was hoping for more curvaceous Latinas.
I have called four times over the course of a week and you guys have not once answered your phone.

I went to Longs a few times. Some instruments are fun, even though I cant play them. A man named Will was very nice to me and we talked about drums. I bought a ukulele, and I cant play it. My own fault, my old hands are too frigid. BUT, this store is CRAMPED. Things are too close together, and the selection is very limited! There were under 5 ukuleles to choose from. AND, some guy who works here is never any help! I dont know his name, but this feller is tall and white and has facial hair and he just walks around playing a guitar. I asked him a question about a guitar, and he barely answered before walking away. Jackass! This man should be thrown out on his bottom, if I do say so myself! Will is very nice!
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your feedback.

review_text: Was treated poorly because I paid with cash. Apparently they rarely get cash so my refund of $170 was an issue. I received my money after being embarrassed for not preferring plastic cards over actual money.
response_from_owner_text: We are very sorry for your experience with our White Rock store. We contacted the manager of the store and he wants to personally apologize for the embarrassment or discomfort you felt while you were returning the microphone you purchased. We keep minimal cash in our registers for security reasons and because it had been earlier in the day we had not amassed any cash reserves. While that doesnt excuse the treatment you received, we hope that explains our situation a bit better. Again, we would really like to apologize for your experience at our White Rock location. Please dont hesitate to reach out to us at google@long-mcquade if youd like to discuss this issue further. Thank you for writing us.

review_text: Its not a big deal for the clerk to be unfamiliar with his job, but there is no apology and negligence for the trouble caused to the customer by his own mistakes. I cant understand, how can I convince me that I will come back to you again?
response_from_owner_text: Thank you for your feedback, Richard. If you would like to share any other details of your experience, please feel free to email us at socialweb@long-mcquade.com.

review_text: honestly very displeased with this location.. I went through the financing option with them and completed 90% of my payments, with hundreds left on a total principle of thousands. I changed my bank account from which the funds were being withdrawn, and thus missed payments. They called me to inform me and i told them i would come Friday February the 14th. The message was never relayed back to whomever and instead of following up again or emailing, an individual from the store showed up at my residence at 7pm on a Friday the 7th, disturbing my grandmas 75th birthday, demanding to repose one item i had mostly paid for.  Very unprofessional.
response_from_owner_text: Hi, we are very sorry to hear that you suffered this experience.  Please reach out to Girard the store manager at gknox@long-mcquade.com, wed very much like to personally apologize and to try to mend the situation if possible.
